Clearly this is just my opinion and I’m sure there will plenty of people who disagree. Here are the spots I would take my chances on hitting a bull with an arrow vs where not to hit them. .1 spot to probably not recover a bull is a neck shot unless you get lucky and hit the jugular or wind pipe. 2. If you hit the scapula or brisket most likely won’t recover it. 3. If you hit high in the void area and don’t hit the main artery under the spine. 1. For recovery obviously heart/lungs. 2. A liver shot will take time depending on how much of it you hit. 3 guy shot! You will most definitely get another chance at a gut shot animal you will just have to give it plenty of time. They will get sick and lay down. Do not rush this time and get that adrenaline going. 4 if you can do major damage to a leg especially a front leg can run them down. An elk is too heavy for their front legs to keep them going very long. They can go a good ways on one back leg but can usually catch up to them again. #bullridge
